\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 29. S. verbenaca} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 25 (1753) ({\i S. clandestina} L., {\i S. horminoides} Pourret, {\i S. controversa }sensu Willk., non Ten.). Stems 10-80 cm, erect, simple or branched, eglandular-pubescent below, and more or less glandular above. Leaves more or less pinnatifid with wide lobes, oblong to ovate. Inflorescence dense or lax; verticillasters with 6-10 flowers. Bracts shorter than calyx, green; pedicels 2-3 mm. Flowers hermaphrodite or female, sometimes cleistogamous. Calyx 6-8 mm, glandular or eglandular, enlarging slightly in fruit. Corolla 6-10(-15) mm, blue, lilac or violet. 2n = 42, 59, 60, 64. {\i  S. & W. Europe, northwards to Scotland.} Al Bl Br Bu Co Cr Ga Gr Hb Hs It Ju Lu Rs (K) Sa Si Tu.
\par

