\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 30. S. nutans} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 27 (1753). Stems up to 170 cm, erect, simple, appressed-hairy, eglandular, leafless above. Leaves simple, long-petiolate, ovate to oblong, cordate at base, irregularly crenate or serrate. Inflorescence nodding at apex before anthesis; verticillasters with 4-6 flowers. Calyx 5-8 mm, shortly villous and punctate-glandular. Corolla 12-16 mm, violet; upper lip suberect. •{\i  From C. Hungary and S.W. Bulgaria eastwards to E.C. Russia.} Bu Hu ?Ju Rm Rs (C, W, K, E) Tu.
