\pard\f0\fs28   Sect. HEMISPHACE Bentham. Perennial herbs. Calyx tubular or campanulate, deflexed in fruit. Upper lip of corolla more or less straight; tube with a ring of hairs inside. Staminal connective longer than and not articulating with filament; arms unequal, the shorter subulate.
\par

