\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 35. S. verticillata} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 26 (1753) ({\i S. peloponnesiaca} Boiss. & Heldr.). Stems up to 80 cm, erect, often simple, eglandular-hairy. Leaves simple, or lyrate with 1-2 pairs of small lateral segments, petiolate, ovate-triangular, cordate to truncate at base, acute. Verticillasters with (8-)15-30 flowers. Pedicels 4-6 mm. Calyx c. 6 mm, with eglandular hairs and sessile glands. Corolla 8-15 mm, lilac-blue; tube slightly exserted; upper lip narrowed at base. 2n = 16.{\i  S., E. & E.C. Europe; naturalized further north.} Al Au Bu Cz Ga Gr Hs Hu It Ju Po Rm Rs (C, W, K, E) Si Tu [Be Br Da Ge *He Ho No Rs (B) Su].
\par

