\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 36. S. napifolia} Jacq.,{\i  Hort. Vindob.}{\b  2}: 71 (1772). Stems up to 100 cm, branched above, glandular-pubescent below, eglandular-villous above. Leaves simple, or lyrate with 1-2 pairs of small lateral segments, petiolate, ovate-triangular, glandular-viscid. Verticillasters with 6-12 flowers. Pedicels 3-5 mm. Calyx 6-8 mm, often violet, with eglandular hairs and sessile glands. Corolla 10-16 mm, violet-blue; tube exserted; upper lip not narrowed at base.{\i  Turkey-in-Europe} ({\i Istanbul region}). Tu. ({\i S.W. Asia.})
